# Leadership Pillar Commentary

## We Take Ownership

Throughout the first half of the year, I significantly expanded my leadership responsibilities by driving the strategic direction and delivery of the firm's Container Security platform portfolio. In addition to leading VSaaS, 3PiiP, and the UBI platform, I extended my ownership to multiple strategic initiatives including Docker Improvement Presets (DiP), Hard Gating integration within LSE/Harness CI/CD pipelines, Middleware Base Image Upliftment, Operator Pipeline migration to 3PiiP, Container Hub Reporting (CHRIS), VSaaS scalability and resiliency improvements, and the adoption of GenAI capabilities across our engineering ecosystem.

These initiatives have been delivered while leading a lean team of four engineers, requiring strong prioritization, execution discipline, and continuous adaptation to changing business priorities. Recognizing the growing demand for our platforms, I partnered closely with HR to expand the team and successfully hired two additional engineers who are expected to join in Q3, strengthening our long-term delivery capability.

I continue to invest in my own leadership development by participating in the iLead program, expanding my leadership skills, organizational network, and ability to influence across the firm. I have also embraced new technologies by championing the adoption of GenAI engineering tools such as Squad, Devin, Stylus, and GitHub Copilot, integrating them into our software development lifecycle to improve engineering productivity and quality.

## We Deliver With Pride

My focus this year has been on creating long-term value through platform modernization, standardization, and operational excellence. I have driven the enterprise adoption of UBI 9 Minimal and Micro base images, partnering closely with Middleware and Artifactory teams to ensure internal base images are secure, compliant, and optimized. By introducing engineering best practices such as multi-stage container builds, jlink patterns, and the removal of unnecessary Java runtimes, we have significantly reduced image sizes, lowered CVE exposure, and improved the overall efficiency of our container ecosystem.

I have continued to strengthen the reliability and scalability of VSaaS, which now processes over 300,000 image scans each month, through performance optimization, resiliency hardening, and platform improvements that support continued growth while maintaining operational excellence.

Beyond engineering delivery, I expanded my role by partnering with our Project Manager to strengthen governance across the Container Security portfolio, ensuring product roadmaps, PTS compliance, and strategic initiatives remain aligned with organizational objectives while proactively addressing technical debt and operational risk.

## We Succeed Together

Collaboration and enablement have been central themes of my leadership approach. I partnered closely with the SRE organization to establish an end-to-end operational support model for VSaaS and 3PiiP, defining clear processes, responsibilities, and support procedures that improve platform reliability and operational maturity.

I have also worked across multiple engineering organizations to accelerate adoption of strategic capabilities. VSaaS became the first team to adopt the Release-on-Demand (RoD) platform, after which I actively supported the onboarding of the Aquatic and Vault teams, helping them modernize their production delivery processes and share best practices across organizations.

Recognizing the importance of developing talent, I onboarded our new Product Owner, Avtar, enabling him to quickly become effective within the Container Security portfolio and assume ownership responsibilities. As an Engineering Excellence (E3) alumnus, I continue to contribute back to the program by serving as a role player and mentor, helping develop future engineering leaders and promoting a culture of continuous learning.

Across all initiatives, I have focused on breaking down organizational barriers, fostering strong partnerships with Middleware, Artifactory, SRE, Product Management, and engineering teams, and creating scalable solutions that deliver lasting value for developers and the broader organization.
